about.summary: Human friendly output for text interfaces using Python.

name: humanfriendly
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.44.7" %}

package:
    name: humanfriendly
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    fn: humanfriendly-1.44.7.tar.gz
    url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/h/humanfriendly/humanfriendly-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: fcee758612edc6fead9b8fd1d5a473eab2c3a84cf8766f3ce70862ccd35e8a64

build:
    number: 2
    script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt
    entry_points:
        - humanfriendly = humanfriendly.cli:main

requirements:
    build:
        - python
        - setuptools
    run:
        - python

test:
    imports:
        - humanfriendly
    commands:
        - humanfriendly --help  # [not osx]
    requires:
        - capturer >=2.1  # [not win]
        - coloredlogs >=2.0

about:
    home: https://humanfriendly.readthedocs.org
    license: MIT
    summary: 'Human friendly output for text interfaces using Python.'

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - ocefpaf
